	dprr:hasNoteText "Their rogation forced an investigation of charges of peculation against L. Scipio and his staff (Antias, fr. 45 Peter, in Liv. 38.50-55, 56, and 58.1; 39.56.3-4; Gell. 4.18.7-12; cf. Polyb. 23.14; FOR 1.10-12, and 147-150; Val. Max. 3.7.1; 5.3.2; Plut. Cat. M. 15.1-2; Apophth. Scip. 10; App. Syr. 40; Gell. 6.19.1-2; Dio fr. 63; Auct. Vir. Ill. 49.17; Zon. 9.21)." .
